Trans fat is the common name for a type of unsaturated fat with trans-isomer fatty acid(s).
The term trans fat generally refers to a fat that contains one or more trans fatty acid groups.
Their 2002 Dietary reference intakes for Energy, Carbohydrate, Fiber, Fat, Fatty Acids, Cholesterol, Protein, and Amino Acids contains their findings and recommendations regarding consumption of trans fat (summary).
